  <compounddef id="TERMWIDTH" kind="page">
    <compoundname>TERMWIDTH</compoundname>
    <title>TERMWIDTH Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">TERMWIDTH</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the <bold>width</bold> of the current terminal, measured in <bold>character columns</bold>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="TERMWIDTH_1autotoc_md432">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Terminal<sp/>width<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>TERMWIDTH</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Draw<sp/>a<sp/>border<sp/>along<sp/>the<sp/>top<sp/>of<sp/>the<sp/>screen</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">CURSOR<sp/>1,<sp/>1</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>STRING$(TERMWIDTH,<sp/>&quot;-&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Centre<sp/>text<sp/>horizontally</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">midX<sp/>=<sp/>TERMWIDTH<sp/>/<sp/>2<sp/>-<sp/>(LEN(&quot;Hello,<sp/>world!&quot;)<sp/>/<sp/>2)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">CURSOR<sp/>midX,<sp/>TERMHEIGHT<sp/>/<sp/>2</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Hello,<sp/>world!&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="TERMWIDTH_1autotoc_md434">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Value is returned as an integer ≥ 1.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Useful for horizontal positioning with <ref refid="CURSOR" kindref="compound">CURSOR</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Works together with <ref refid="TERMHEIGHT" kindref="compound">TERMHEIGHT</ref> to adapt output to the current terminal size.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
